After import, `dataVEET2` contains columns for the timestamp (`Datetime`), `Gain` (the sensor gain setting), and the nine spectral sensor channels plus the two clear channels and dark channel (as described earlier). These appear as numeric columns named `s415, s445, ..., s940, Dark, ClearL, ClearR`. The spectral sensor was logging at the same 2-second rate. Because this dataset is even denser and more high-dimensional, we will **aggregate it to a 5-minute interval** for computational efficiency. The assumption is that spectral composition does not need to be examined at every 2-second instant for our purposes, and 5-minute averages can capture the general trends while drastically reducing data size and downstream computational costs.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
# Aggregate spectral data to 5-minute intervals and mark gaps
dataVEET2 <- dataVEET2 |>
  aggregate_Datetime(unit = "5 mins") |>     # aggregate to 5-minute bins
  gap_handler(full.days = TRUE) |>           # explicit NA for any gaps in between
  add_Date_col(group.by = TRUE) |> 
  remove_partial_data(ClearR, threshold.missing = "1 hour")
```
:::



We aggregate over 5-minute windows; within each 5-minute bin, multiple spectral readings (if present) are combined (averaged). We use one of the channels (here `ClearR`) as the reference variable for `remove_partial_data` to drop incomplete days (the choice of channel is arbitrary as all channels share the same level of completeness). After this, `dataVEET2` too covers the same six full days as `dataVEET` and `dataCC`.

It is informative to look at a snippet of the imported spectral data before further processing. @tbl-PHO shows the first three rows of `dataVEET2` after import (before calibration), with some technical columns omitted for brevity:



::: {#tbl-PHO .cell tbl-cap='Overview of the spectral sensor import from the VEET device (first 3 observations). Each row corresponds to a 5-minute timestamp (Datetime) and shows the raw sensor readings for the spectral channels (s415–s940, Dark, ClearL, ClearR). All values are in arbitrary sensor units (counts). Gain values and integration_time are also relevant for each interval, depending on the downstream computation.'}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
#| label: tbl-PHO
#| tbl-cap: "Overview of the spectral sensor import from the VEET device (first 3 observations). Each row corresponds to a 5-minute timestamp (Datetime) and shows the raw sensor readings for the spectral channels (s415–s940, Dark, ClearL, ClearR). All values are in arbitrary sensor units (counts). Gain values and integration_time are also relevant for each interval, depending on the downstream computation."
dataVEET2 |> head(3) |> select(-c(modality, file.name, is.implicit, time_stamp)) |> 
  gt() |> fmt_number(s415:ClearR) 
```

